label: Study-defined diarrhea
definition: Whether the participant had diarrhea on this day of observation, defined in the MAL-ED study as having more than 2 loose stools in the day or, if there was blood in the stool, having 1-2 loose stools in the day. Since Lactulose:Mannitol (L:M) causes loose stools, days with Lactulose:Mannitol (L:M)-induced diarrhea (where the participant met the definition of diarrhea but had an Lactulose:Mannitol (L:M) test on that day or the previous day) were not classified as study-defined diarrhea. Surveillance was conducted twice weekly for up to 3 years of age to assess illness on all days since the last surveillance visit.

label: Total days in all diarrheal episodes
definition: Total number of days that fall within any diarrheal episode since beginning of follow-up. Diarrhea episodes were separated by two diarrhea-free days. Surveillance was conducted twice weekly for up to 3 years of age to assess illness on all days since the last surveillance visit.

label: Bacteriology testing completed
definition: Whether this stool sample underwent all bacteriology tests. Stool samples must have a completed Campylobacter ELISA test in addition to culture for Salmonella, Shigella, Vibrio, Yersinia, Aeromonas, and Plesiomonas for bacteriology testing to be considered complete. After culture, suspicious colonies were screened by biochemical tests to identify bacterial species. All presumptive Salmonella, Shigella, and Vibrio were confirmed by serotyping. Yersinia, Aeromonas, and Plesiomonas were confirmed by supplemental biochemical tests. Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. Work up for detection of enteric pathogens was performed on the first stool sample collected during each diarrheal episode until 24 months of age (with a possible extension to 36 months of age) and on first monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age (with the option to test additional monthly stool samples to 36 months of age).

Work up for detection of enteric pathogens was performed on the first stool sample collected during each diarrheal episode until 24 months of age (with a possible extension to 36 months of age) and on first monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age (with the option to test additional monthly stool samples to 36 months of age).
codebook_description: Was Vibrio detected?. From BDF form. Information comes from first collected sample, if there was a recollection sample. ''Vibrio'' is the variable name for bdfvibtype collapsed into a yes/no variable. Source=BDF. yes, vibrio cholerae 01, inaba =01; yes, vibrio cholerae 01, ogawa =02; yes, vibrio cholerae 0139 =03; yes, vibrio para =04; yes, vibrio (all others)=05; no =00

Work up for detection of enteric pathogens was performed on the first stool sample collected during each diarrheal episode until 24 months of age (with a possible extension to 36 months of age) and on first monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age (with the option to test additional monthly stool samples to 36 months of age).

label: Analysis stool, monthly
definition: Whether this was the first asymptomatic stool sample collected for a specific month and microbiology testing was completed according to the MAL-ED protocol. label: Monthly stool collection #
definition: The Nth stool collected in the sequence of asymptomatic monthly stool samples collected for a specific month, regardless of protocol. Occasionally, more than one non-diarrheal stool sample is collected in a specific month. Monthly asymptomatic stool samples were collected every month from 0-24 months of age, with a possible extension to 36 months of age.

label: Stool type, physiologic
definition: Type of stool type collected, using information from surveillance. 'Diarrhea stools' were samples with a liquid or watery consistency where diarrhea was reported within +/- 2 days of stool collection. 'Monthly stools' were collected more than 2 days away from an episode of study-defined diarrhea. Surveillance was conducted twice weekly for up to 3 years of age to assess illness on all days since the last surveillance visit. Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. Work up for detection of enteric pathogens was performed on diarrheal stool samples collected until 24 months of age (with a possible extension to 36 months of age) and on first monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age (with the option to test additional monthly stool samples to 36 months of age).
codebook_description: Type of stool sample collected. Using information from surveillance. Diarrhea stool = diarrhea reported within +/- 2 days from stool collection plus having a liquid or watery consistency. Monthly stool is stool collected more than 2 days away from study defined diarrhea. Source=Calculated. m1 =monthly; d1=diarrhea stool with watery or liquid consistency

label: Per protocol diarrheal stool collection
definition: Whether this diarrheal stool sample was collected per the MAL-ED study protocol. Per protocol diarrheal stools included samples collected before the end of each diarrheal episode (whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day) as well as additional stool samples collected for a specific diarrhea episode after 14 study-defined diarrhea days in the same episode. Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. Diarrheal stool samples were collected until 36 months of age.

label: Cumulative per protocol diarrheal stool count
definition: Cumulative count of the number of stool samples collected per the MAL-ED study protocol to date. Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. Diarrheal stool samples were collected until 36 months of age.

label: Cumulative stool count

First monthly asymptomatic stool samples were collected every month from 0-24 months of age, with a possible extension to 36 months of age. Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. Diarrheal stool samples were collected until 36 months of age.

variable: f2 hosp | BC-3 mothers all visits database FINAL::mhosp | hospitalized | illnessfull::hosp
codebook_description: was the mother hospitalized today | Patient refered for hospitalization | Hospitalized | REF - child was hospitalized on this day

label: Any parasites, by modified acid stain microscopy
definition: Whether this stool sample had any parasites detected by modified acid fast stain microscopy. Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. Work up for detection of enteric pathogens was performed on the first stool sample collected during each diarrheal episode until 24 months of age (with a possible extension to 36 months of age) and on first monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age (with the option to test additional monthly stool samples to 36 months of age).
codebook_description: Were any pathogens detected by modified acid fast stain?. Collapsed variable for mdfstaindetect. Source=Calculated. 1=yes;0=no

label: Campylobacter, by ELISA
definition: Whether Campylobacter was detected by ELISA for this stool sample. Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. Work up for detection of enteric pathogens was performed on the first stool sample collected during each diarrheal episode until 24 months of age (with a possible extension to 36 months of age) and on first monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age (with the option to test additional monthly stool samples to 36 months of age).
codebook_description: Campylobacter detected using ELISA?. Use this Campylobacter variable (campy) for analysis. Per microbiology committee, use only ELISA results for analysis. Source=Calculated. 1=yes;0=no

label: Exclusively breastfed at 1st day of surveillance
definition: Whether the participant was exclusively breastfeeding on the 1st day of bi-weekly breastfeeding surveillance data collection. Baseline breastfeeding information was collected upon enrollment.
codebook_description: Indicates whether exclusive breastfeeding was present on day of first SAF data collection, the age at which this occurred is the minage. Source=calculated.

label: Breastfed within 1st 24hrs
definition: Whether the participant began breastfeeding within 24 hours after birth. Baseline breastfeeding information was collected upon enrollment.
codebook_description: Whether the child began breastfeeding within 24 hours per the CAF. Source=calculated.

label: Time between childbirth and 1st breastfeeding
definition: How long after childbirth did the mother begin breastfeeding the participant. Baseline breastfeeding information was collected upon enrollment.
codebook_description: How long after childbirth did the mother begin breastfeeding him/her. Source=CAF. 0=within 1 hr; 1=1-24hrs; 2=1-3days; 3=4+ days later

label: Fed colostrum
definition: Whether the participant was fed the first milk (colostrum). Baseline breastfeeding information was collected upon enrollment.
codebook_description: Was the child fed the first milk (colostrum)?. Source=CAF.

label: Prelacteal feeding
definition: Whether there was prelacteal feeding of the participant. Baseline breastfeeding information was collected upon enrollment.
codebook_description: Was there prelacteal feeding of the child?. Source=CAF.

label: Cumulative days exclusively breastfed
definition: Cumulative sum of days with exclusive breastfeeding (ie, number of days, from birth to date, that the participant was reported to be exclusively breastfed). Between birth and the 1st bi-weekly breastfeeding survey, participants who began breastfeeding at all were considered to be exclusively breastfed. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age. | Assessed at each week of observation and prior to each diarrheal episode.
variable: ext mgmt bv ddep st::epiexlbf | bf2::cumexc | ext mgmt bv danth::vstexlbf
codebook_description: Number of exclusive breastfeeding days prior to the episode | Cumulative days of exclusive breastfeeding from birth. This is a cumulative sum of the variable ''excrun'', i.e., number of days, to date from birth, that the child was reported to be exclusively breastfed. This has been filled in between birth and minage with EBF if child began breastfeeding at all (cafbegbf~=.). Exclusive breastfeeding prevalence can be calculated by dividing cumexc / age (or days of follow up). This is a cumulative sum so that we can merge this dataset with others and determine what percent of the time a child was exclusively, predominantly, partially, and not breastfed prior to some outcome (anthro, illness, etc.).. Source=calculated. | Number of exclusive breastfeeding days at that visit

label: Cumulative days not breastfed
definition: Cumulative sum of days with no breastfeeding (ie, number of days, from birth to date, that the participant was reported to not be breastfed). Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.
codebook_description: Cumulative days of no breastfeeding (cumulative sum of nobfrun, ie, number of days from birth, to date, that the child was reported to not be breastfed).. This is a cumulative sum so that we can merge this dataset with others and determine what percent of the time a child was exclusively, predominantly, partially, and not breastfed prior to some outcome (anthro, illness, etc.).. Source=calculated.

label: Cumulative days partially breastfed
definition: Cumulative sum of days with partial breastfeeding (ie, number of days, from birth to date, that the participant was reported to be partially breastfed). Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.
codebook_description: Cumulative days of partial breastfeeding (cumulative sum of partrun, ie, number of days, to date, that the child was reported to be partially breastfed).. New predominant and partial variables considering animal milk to be ingested with tea in Pakistan (even if animal milk is not indicated on the SAF). Source=calculated.

label: Cumulative days predominantly breastfed
definition: Cumulative sum of days with predominant breastfeeding (ie, number of days, from birth to date, that the participant was reported to be predominantly breastfed). Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.
codebook_description: Cumulative days of predominant breastfeeding (cumulative sum of predrun, ie, number of days, to date, that the child was reported to be predominantly breastfed).. New predominant and partial variables considering animal milk to be ingested with tea in Pakistan (even if animal milk is not indicated on the SAF). Source=calculated.

label: Dairy reported at last visit
definition: Whether presence of dairy (milk, formula, yogurt, cheese, or other dairy products) in the diet was reported at the last breastfeeding surveillance visit. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.
codebook_description: Dairy intake (milk, formula, yogurt, cheese, or other dairy products, as reported on the SAF or MOA). This is a simple variable that reflects the presence of dairy in the diet at last reported diet day.. Source=calculated.

label: Exclusively breastfed at last visit
definition: Whether exclusive breastfeeding (breastfeeding present with no other liquids or solids) was reported at the last visit. Participants could switch back and forth between exclusive and different types of non-exclusive breastfeeding. Data between breastfeeding surveillance visits were filled in forward. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.
codebook_description: Exclusive breastfeeding (breastfeeding present, no liquid, no solids). This is a simple variable that reflects the exclusive breastfeeding status at last reported diet day. Children can switch back and forth between exclusive and different types of non-exclusive breastfeeding.. These variables provide the breastfeeding category at the last visit (since data between visits are filled in forward).. Source=calculated.

label: Age at 1st day of biweekly breastfeeding surveillance (days)
definition: Minimum age in days at which bi-weekly breastfeeding surveillance data is available. Baseline breastfeeding information was collected upon enrollment.
codebook_description: Minimum age in days at which SAF diet data is available. Source=calculated.

label: Age 1st animal milk or formula given (days)
definition: Age in days at which first animal milk (including animal milk ingested with tea in Pakistan) or formula was given. This variable changed feeding definitions for 'Breastfeeding status' and 'Age last exclusively breastfed (days)' starting with the first occasion animal milk or formula were given, and did not allow for back and forth. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.
codebook_description: Age at which first milk is given. New predominant and partial variables considering animal milk to be ingested with tea in Pakistan (even if animal milk is not indicated on the SAF). Source=calculated.

label: Age at complete weaning (days)
definition: Age in days at which breastfeeding ceases (complete weaning), if observed at all. This variable changed feeding definitions for 'Breastfeeding status' and 'Age last exclusively breastfed (days)' starting with the first occasion complete weaning was observed, and did not allow for back and forth. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.
codebook_description: Age at which breastfeeding ceases (complete weaning: if observed in data set at all). These calculations change feeding definitions starting with the first occasion.  They do not allow for back and forth.. Source=calculated.

label: Age 1st animal milk or solids given (days)
definition: Age in days at which first animal milk (including animal milk ingested with tea in Pakistan) OR solids was given. This variable changed feeding definitions for 'Breastfeeding status' and 'Age last exclusively breastfed (days)' starting with the first occasion animal milk or solids were given, and did not allow for back and forth. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.
codebook_description: Age at which first milk OR solids is given. New predominant and partial variables considering animal milk to be ingested with tea in Pakistan (even if animal milk is not indicated on the SAF). Source=calculated.

label: Age 1st clear liquid given (days)
definition: Age in days at which first clear liquid is given. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.
codebook_description: Age at which first clear liquid is given. New predominant and partial variables considering animal milk to be ingested with tea in Pakistan (even if animal milk is not indicated on the SAF). Source=calculated.

label: Age 1st solid food given (days)
definition: Age in days at which first solid food is given. label: Not breastfed at last visit
definition: Whether no breastfeeding was reported at the last visit. Participants could switch back and forth between exclusive and different types of non-exclusive breastfeeding. Data between breastfeeding surveillance visits were filled in forward. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.

label: Partially breastfed at last visit
definition: Whether partial breastfeeding (breastfeeding present with solids, animal milk (considering animal milk to be ingested with tea in Pakistan), and/or formula) was reported at the last visit. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.

New predominant and partial variables considering animal milk to be ingested with tea in Pakistan (even if animal milk is not indicated on the SAF). Source=calculated.

label: Predominantly breastfed at last visit
definition: Whether predominant breastfeeding (breastfeeding and clear liquids (water, fruit juice, tea, other liquids) present, with no solids, animal milk (considering animal milk to be ingested with tea in Pakistan), or formula) was reported at the last visit. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.

This is a simple variable that reflects the breastfeeding status at last reported diet day.. New predominant and partial variables considering animal milk to be ingested with tea in Pakistan (even if animal milk is not indicated on the SAF). Source=calculated.

label: Breastfeeding status
definition: Breastfeeding status was changed starting with the first occasion clear liquid, animal milk, formula, or solid food were given, and did not allow for back and forth. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.
codebook_description: These calculations change feeding definitions starting with the first occasion.  They do not allow for back and forth.. Source=calculated. 0 during exclusive breastfeeding, 1 when any non-breast milk feeding starts until last breastmilk reported, 2 after last breast milk is ingested.t

label: Age last exclusively breastfed (days)
definition: Maximum age in days of imputed exclusive breastfeeding (liquid or food given on next day), only including participants who were reported to be given non-breast milk foods. Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.

label: Breastfeeding data present today
definition: Whether breastfeeding data was present today or not. Data were generally collected for yesterday's diet (ie, the day prior to the day the field worker is in the home). Breastfeeding surveillance occurred twice per week throughout 24 or 36 months of age.
codebook_description: Whether the data was present today (1) or not (0). For bf, data were generally collected for yesterday's diet, ie, the day prior to the day the field worker is in the home.. Source=calculated. 1=yes, 0=no.

label: Results from all gut inflammation tests available
definition: Whether results from alpha-1-antitrypsin, myeloperoxidase, and neopterin gut inflammation biomarker tests are available for the stool sample. To be included in the gut function analysis set used in PMID: 28396264, results from all 3 biomarker tests must be available. Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. First monthly asymptomatic stool samples were collected every month from 0-24 months of age, with a possible extension to 36 months of age. First monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age were included in analyses of gut function.

label: Diarrheal stool
definition: Whether this stool sample was considered a diarrheal stool by the MAL-ED Gut Function Technical Subcommittee. Stools that were collected on a day that falls within a diarrheal episode or where the last diarrheal episode ended less than or equal to 7 days ago met this definition. Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. First monthly asymptomatic stool samples were collected every month from 0-24 months of age, with a possible extension to 36 months of age.
codebook_description: 1 if considered a diarrhea stool (dprev3=1 or 1<= lastdiar <=7) ; 0 otherwise . Source=calculated.

label: Urine included in L:M analysis
definition: Flag for Lactulose:Mannitol (L:M) urine samples that were excluded from analysis. Reasons for exclusion include (i) if either lactulose or mannitol were not detected, (ii) if either lactulose or mannitol excretion was more than 100% of the dosage, (iii) if the duration of urine collection was either less than 4.5 hours or more than 5.5 hours, or (iv) if there was some other known issue with the sample. The Lactulose:Mannitol dual sugar test for gut permeability was used for analysis of environmental enteropathy and was assessed in urine samples collected at 3, 6, 9, and 15 months of age.

label: Diarrhea severity score
definition: Combination of Vesikari and Clark scales for diarrhea within -/+ 2 days of stool collection. Values can range from 1 (least severe) to 14 (most severe). Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. First monthly asymptomatic stool samples were collected every month from 0-24 months of age, with a possible extension to 36 months of age.
codebook_description: severity score for diarrhea days within +/2 days of stool collection. Source=illnessfull.

label: Recollection requested
definition: Reason recollection of the stool sample was requested. Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. First monthly asymptomatic stool samples were collected every month from 0-24 months of age, with a possible extension to 36 months of age.
codebook_description: Was recollection requested?. Source=SRF. yes, monthly specimen <4g = 01, yes, diarrheal specimen <2g = 02, no =00

label: Currency exchange rate to USD
definition: Currency exchange rate to buy US Dollars. Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.

label: Separate kitchen
definition: Whether the dwelling has a separate room which was used as a kitchen, in order to provide additional information on the hygiene status of the household. Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.
codebook_description: Do you have a separate room which is used as a kitchen?. Source=FSE. yes = 01; no = 00

label: Maternal education
definition: Whether the participant's mother had ever attended school. This variable refers to formal school only, and includes any formal schooling beginning with kindergarten. Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.
codebook_description: Have you ever attended school? . Source=FSE. yes = 01; no = 00

label: Maternal education score
definition: Years of schooling that the participant's mother had completed, divided by 2. Used as a component in calculating the WAMI index. Values ranged from 0 (low) to 8 (high). Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.
codebook_description: How many years of schooling have you completed?. Source=FSE. 00-20

label: Income score
definition: Average monthly income for the entire household, converted to US Dollars, categorized into all-site noniles. Used as a component in calculating the WAMI index. Values ranged from 0 (low) to 8 (high). Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.
codebook_description: Reported income in US Dollars, catgeorized in all-site noniles. Source=FSE(derived). income category cutoffs, noniles of ''newincome'' (created using income data up to 36 months):0: <=36.6; 1: >=36.62 & <=65.7; 2: >=65.8 & <=90.9; 3: >=90.972 & <=111.84; 4: >=111.93 & <=140.72; 5: >=140.76 & <=180.65; 6: >=180.8 & <=250; 7: >=250.05 & <=353.2; 8: >=353.338

label: Drinking water score
definition: Whether the household drinking water source was categorized as improved or unimproved, based on WHO definitions. Drinking water sources categorized as 'Improved' include water that is 'Piped into dwelling' or 'Piped into yard or plot,' or from a 'Public tap or stand pipe;' a 'Tube well or borehole;' or a 'Protected well.' Drinking water sources categorized as 'Unimproved' include water that is from an 'Unprotected well' or 'Surface water.' Other sources of drinking water were considered 'Improved,' except for Peru where it was considered 'Unimproved' due to site-specific circumstances. Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.
codebook_description: Score of drinking water source; 0  for unimproved categories, 4 for improved categories. Source=FSE(derived). if fsewdrink = ''01'',''02'',''03'',''04'',''05'',''08'' then newdrink=4, ''improved'' except for pel where fsewdrink=''08'' is also considered unimproved due to site-specific circumstances; if fsewdrink = ''06'',''07'' then newdrink=0 ''unimproved'', except for pel where values of ''08'' for fsewdrink are considered unimproved

label: Mean people per room
definition: Mean number of people sleeping in each room in the dwelling. Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months. | Mean number of persons per room used for sleeping. Determined for households surveyed at baseline only.
codebook_description: Number of persons per room used for sleeping | Mean number of people per room in the household (fsesleep/fseroom1). Source=FSE(derived). #

label: Maternal education (years)
definition: Years of schooling that the participant's mother had completed, beginning with kindergarten and through any university or post-university education. Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months. | Number of years of education completed by the target child participant's mother. Assessed for the household at enrollment (when target children were in utero).
codebook_description: Mother, years of education (q009)

label: Family income (USD)
definition: Average monthly income for the entire household, converted to US Dollars. Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.
codebook_description: Reported income mulitplied by exchange rate. Source=FSE(derived). #

label: Sanitation score
definition: Whether the household sanitation facilities were classified as improved or unimproved, based on WHO definitions. Sanitation facilities categorized as 'Improved' include those classified as 'Other,' 'Pit latrine without flush/with slab,''Flush to piped sewer system,' 'Flush to septic tank,' 'Flush to pit latrine,' or 'Flush to somewhere else.' 'No facility/bush/field or bucket toilet/pit latrine without slab' was considered 'Unimproved.' Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.
codebook_description: Score of sanitation; 0 for unimproved categories, 4 for improved categories. Source=FSE(derived). if fsetoiletmod = ''01'' then newsanitation=0, unimproved;if fsetoiletmod = ''02'',''03'',''04'',''05'',''06'',''07'' then newsanitation=4, improved

label: Overall socioeconomic score
definition: Sum of all 4 components used to calculate the WAMI index: (i) 'Sanitation and drinking water score,' (ii) 'Assets score,' (iii) 'Income score,' and (iv) 'Maternal education score.' Values ranged from 0 (low) to 32 (high). Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.
codebook_description: sum of all WAMI component scores. Source=FSE(derived). 0-32

label: Fewer than 2 people per room
definition: Whether fewer than 2 people, on average, sleep in each room in the dwelling. Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.
codebook_description: Score of 1 if less than 2 people (mean) per room. Source=FSE(derived). #

label: Sanitation and drinking water score
definition: Sum of sanitation and drinking water scores. Used as a component in calculating the WAMI index. Households with 'Drinking water categorization' and 'Sanitation categorization' variables classified as 'improved' got a score of 4 for each; 'unimproved' responses got a score of 0 for each. Values ranged from 0 (low) to 8 (high). Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.
codebook_description: Sum of saniation and drinking scores. . Source=FSE(derived). range 0-8

label: WAMI index
definition: An index of socio-economic status that includes access to improved water and sanitation, eight selected assets, maternal education, and household income. The WAMI index was calculated by dividing the 'Overall socioeconomic score' by 32. Values ranged from 0 (low) to 1 (high). Socioeconomic status was assessed every 6 months from 6-24 months and again at 60 months of age, with optional assessments from 30-60 months.
codebook_description: The wami is calculated by summing values of the following variables: sanitation, asset, incat, newfseschool and dividing the total by 32. Source=FSE(derived). range 0-1

label: Stool type, gut function
definition: Stool type definition from the MAL-ED Gut Function Technical Subcommittee. 'Other stools' were samples where diarrhea was reported within the preceding 7 days and/or the lactulose:mannitol test was performed on the day of or day before stool collection. 'Asymptomatic stools' were stool samples that did not meet this definition of 'Other stools.' Only 'Asymptomatic stools' were included in the gut function analysis set used in PMID: 28396264. Surveillance was conducted twice weekly for up to 3 years of age to assess illness on all days since the last surveillance visit. Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. First monthly asymptomatic stool samples were collected every month from 0-24 months of age, with a possible extension to 36 months of age. First monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age were included in analyses of gut function.
codebook_description: gut function committee stool type definition 0 = asymptomatic; 1 if diarrhea within the preceding 7 days and/or LM test on the day of or day before stool collection. Source=calculated.

label: Stool used for environmental enteropathy analysis
definition: Indicator to select the gut function analysis set of stool samples used in PMID: 28396264. Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. First monthly asymptomatic stool samples were collected every month from 0-24 months of age, with a possible extension to 36 months of age. First monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age were included in analyses of gut function.
codebook_description: indicator variable 1 if the first stool for a given child/month; NA otherwise; used to select analysis set. Source=calculated.

label: Per protocol stool collection
definition: Whether this was a per protocol stool collection, as defined by the MAL-ED Gut Function Technical Subcommittee. Per protocol first monthly asymptomatic stool samples were collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age. Per protocol diarrhea stool samples were collected on a day that falls within a diarrheal episode or where the last diarrheal episode ended less than or equal to 7 days ago.
codebook_values: 1 =asymptomatic stool age (1-12, 15, 18, 21, 24m); 2=diarrheal 2 (diarrhea_gf=1); NA otherwise . Source=calculated. 1=included; 2=excluded, na = excluded

label: Mean ferritin (ng/mL)
definition: Mean concentration of ferritin in the blood (ng/mL). When 'Ferritin (ng/mL), 2nd' is not available, 'Mean ferritin (ng/mL)' is equal to 'Ferritin (ng/mL).' Micronutrient status was assessed in blood samples collected at 7, 15, 24, and 36 months of age.
codebook_description: Mean (FARVAL1, FARVAL2), blood.

label: Low ferritin (less than 12ng/mL)
definition: Concentration of ferritin in the blood is less than 12ng/mL. Micronutrient status was assessed in blood samples collected at 7, 15, 24, and 36 months of age.
codebook_description: 1= FARVAL1 <12; 0= FARVAL1>=12, blood.

label: Low retinol (less than 20ug/dL)
definition: Concentration of retinol in the blood is less than 20ug/dL. Micronutrient status was assessed in blood samples collected at 7, 15, 24, and 36 months of age.
codebook_description: 1= RARCONC <20; 0= RARCONC>=20, blood.

label: Low zinc (less than 9.9 umol/L)
definition: Concentration of zinc in the blood is less than 9.9umol/L. All zinc data from South Africa has been excluded. Micronutrient status was assessed in blood samples collected at 7, 15, 24, and 36 months of age.
codebook_description: 1= zinc_mml<9.9; 0= zinc_mml>=9.9, blood.

label: Retinol (ug/dL)
definition: Concentration of retinol in the blood (ug/dL). Micronutrient status was assessed in blood samples collected at 7, 15, 24, and 36 months of age.
codebook_description: 1= adjtfr<2.9; 2=  2.9<= adjtfr < 8.3; 3= adjtfr>=8.3 . Source=calculated.

label: Symptoms by caregiver report
definition: Based on parental recall. Collected for both cases and controls. Blood in stool was restricted to children with diarrhea based on caregiver report.
parent_label: Signs and symptoms | Signs and Symptoms

label: Entamoeba histolytica, by ELISA result
definition: Results of Entamoeba histolytica ELISA for this stool sample. Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. Work up for detection of enteric pathogens was performed on diarrheal stool samples collected until 24 months of age (with a possible extension to 36 months of age) and on first monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age (with the option to test additional monthly stool samples to 36 months of age).
codebook_description: E. histolytica result by ELISA?. Raw variable from PEF form. Use collapsed variable ''ehist'' for analyses. Source=PEF. positive =01; negative =02; indeterminate =03

label: Adjusted soluble transferrin receptor (ug/mL)
definition: Inflammation-adjusted concentration of soluble transferrin receptor (TfR) in the blood (ug/mL), using site specific correction factors based on methods described in PMID: 16313694. Micronutrient status was assessed in blood samples collected at 7, 15, 24, and 36 months of age.
codebook_description: inflammation (AGPVAL>100) adjusted tfr concentration using site specific correction factors*. Correction factors: BG 1.0220263, BR 1.0004088, IN 1.0700322, NP 0.9913484, PE 1.0174282, PK 1.0372579, SA 1.2388953, TZ 1.0305495. Source=calculated.

label: Adjusted soluble transferrin receptor level

label: 24hr food recall survey conducted in target window

label: Urine collected in target window
definition: Urine collected within a -/+ 2 day target window or within a +7 day extended window. Urine samples were collected at 3, 6, 9, 15, 24, and 36 months of age.

Work up for detection of enteric pathogens was performed on diarrheal stool samples collected until 24 months of age (with a possible extension to 36 months of age) and first monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age (with the option to test additional monthly stool samples to 36 months of age).

label: Bacteria in stool
definition: Detection of the following bacteria in stool samples. Work up for detection of enteric pathogens was performed on diarrheal stool samples collected until 24 months of age (with a possible extension to 36 months of age) and first monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age (with the option to test additional monthly stool samples to 36 months of age).

label: Campylobacter, by bacteriology cleaned result
definition: Whether Campylobacter was detected by bacteriology culture for this stool sample (raw identification data from 'Campylobacter, by bacteriology result' was recoded to 'Yes'/'No'). Note: do not use Campylobacter culture results for analysis unless performing a specific analysis investigating Campylobacter in culture. Whenever a participant produced at least 3 loose stools in a single day, diarrheal stool samples were collected before the end of the episode. Work up for detection of enteric pathogens was performed on the first stool sample collected during each diarrheal episode until 24 months of age (with a possible extension to 36 months of age) and on first monthly asymptomatic stool samples collected at 1-12, 15, 18, 21, and 24 months of age (with the option to test additional monthly stool samples to 36 months of age).

label: Number Anopheles gambiae sl tested by PCR
definition: A subset of Anopheles gambiae sl were tested for subspecies identification by PCR. This variable indicates the number of Anopheles gambiae sl from all collections done within a household on a given day. label: Bacteria in nasopharyngeal/oropharyngeal swabs
definition: Common colonizers defined as CMV, H. influenzae, M. pneumoniae, Moraxella species, S. pneumoniae, and S. aureus. Klebsiella pneumoniae was considered a contaminant due to difficulties with assay specificity. For "absolute qPCR" variables, the sample was considered positive if above the qPCR density thresholds (see PERCH publications). H. influenzae - 5.9 log10 copies/mL, S. pneumoniae 6.9 log10 copies/mL.

label: Eukaryota in nasopharyngeal/oropharyngeal swabs
definition: Normalized defined as above the quantitative PCR density thresholds (see PERCH publications). P. jirovecii - 4.0 log10 copies/mL.

label: Virus in nasopharyngeal/oropharyngeal swabs
definition: Common colonizer defined as CMV. Measles testing was only performed on cases who met the clinical criteria for measles testing (history of measles in past month, measles rash, measles admission diagnosis, measles discharge diagnosis). "Absolute qPCR" variables were considered positive if above the qPCR density thresholds (see PERCH publications). CMV - 4.9 log10 copies/mL.

label: O2 saturation level
definition: Oxygen saturation was measured at admission, 24-hour follow-up, and 48-hour follow-up timepoints and only collected for cases. Cases with oxygen saturation measured while on oxygen are categorized with those who had an oxygen saturation 61-91%. Oxygen saturation categories are decreased by 2% for sites are higher altitude (Zambia and South Africa).

label: Severe or very severe pneumonia eligibility
definition: Severe pneumonia was defined as cough or difficulty breathing with lower chest wall indrawing. Very severe pneumonia was defined as cough or difficulty breathing and at least one of the following signs: central cyanosis, difficulty breastfeeding or drinking, vomiting everything, multiple or prolonged convulsions, lethargy or unconsciousness, or head nodding.

label: Lethargic
definition: If the child was lethargic at admission, including 1) responds to voice, 2) responds to pain, or 3) unresponsive. Only collected for cases.

definition: The smallest rural administrative or local government unit in Bangladesh.

label: Compound study arm
definition: The actual randomized, blinded intervention assigned to the compound. Compounds consisted of multiple households (typically 3 to 10 in Bangladesh), usually comprised of blood relatives, who share a common courtyard. Each randomization block was made up of 8 adjacent clusters (groups of 8 proximate compounds) that were pair-matched by geography. Each cluster within the randomization block was randomly allocated to one of 7 study arms, including 2 clusters randomly allocated to the control arm. A description of each study arm can be found on the study details page.
codebook_description: Randomized treatment assignment (actual)

label: LNS consumed
definition: Number of lipid-based nutrient supplement (LNS) sachets consumed by the household per week. Based on counting sachets present at the time of a field visit. The expected number of sachets for 100% adherence is 14 sachets (7 days x 2 sachets per day). Values of LNS consumed that were negative or >28 were flagged.  Assessed for the household 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age).

label: LNS consumed flag
definition: Whether the number of lipid-based nutrient supplement (LNS) sachets consumed by the household per week was flagged for being negative or greater than 28. Assessed for the household 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age).

label: Percent LNS consumed
definition: Percent of expected lipid-based nutrient supplement (LNS) sachets consumed by the household per week. Based on counting sachets present at the time of a field visit. The expected number of sachets for 100% adherence is 14 sachets (7 days x 2 sachets per day). Values of LNS consumed that were negative or >28 were flagged. Assessed for the household 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age).

label: LNS consumed, caregiver report
definition: Number of lipid-based nutrient supplement (LNS) sachets consumed by the household per week, as reported by the mother. Assessed for the household 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age).
codebook_description: LNS sachets consumed per week (reported)

definition: Percent of expected lipid-based nutrient supplement (LNS) sachets consumed by the household, as reported by the mother. label: Diarrhea case during the last 7 days, caregiver report
definition: Did the child have diarrhea in the last week? | Whether the participant was classified as a diarrhea case within the last 7 days. To meet the definition for a diarrhea case, the participant must have had 3+ loose or watery stools in 24 hours OR 1+ stool with blood. This variable, with a 7-day recall period, was used in the primary analysis to improve power as there was no evidence for differential recall by arm. Caregiver reported symptoms were assessed in target children 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age). Caregiver reported symptoms were also assessed in sibling/neighbor participants at enrollment, midline, and endline.
codebook_description: Child had diarrhea in the last week | Child had diarrhea | * Diarrhea case, 7d recall

label: Diarrhea case during the last 2 days, caregiver report
definition: Whether the participant was classified as a diarrhea case within the last 2 days. Caregiver reported symptoms were assessed in target children 1 year after intervention initiation (midline, when target children were 8-15m of age) and 2 years after intervention initiation (endline, when target children were 21-27m of age). Caregiver reported symptoms were also assessed in sibling/neighbor participants at enrollment, midline, and endline.

label: Rotavirus G genotype, by qRT-PCR result
definition: Diarrheal samples positive for rotavirus by both ELISA and TAC assays or just TAC were genotyped using two real time RT-PCR panels; Panel G- G1, G2, G9, G12, NSP3; Panel P-P4, P6, P8, P10, P11. 158 samples were positive by both ELISA and TAC, and 105 samples were positive by only TAC.
codebook_description: G Type Gene Sequence for Rotavirus positive strain using a RT-PCR
codebook_values: 1 = G type 1, 2 = G type 2, 9 = G type 9, 12 = G type 12, 3 = Mixed, 0 = unable to type (-9 = missing data)

codebook_values: 4 = P type 4, 6 = P type 6, 8 = P type 8, 10 = P type 10, 11 = P type 11, 3 = Mixed, 0 = unable to type (-9 = missing data)

label: Cluster as-treated
definition: For households surveyed 6, 12, or 18 months after the 2016-2017 Universal Coverage Campaign (UCC), the type of long-lasting insecticide-treated bednet (LLIN) received by the cluster, for the as-treated analysis. Certain clusters received a different LLIN type than that which was originally assigned to that cluster (the 'Cluster study arm'). For the as-treated analysis, clusters were grouped by type of LLINs received according to household data from the 6-month study timepoint ('UCC LLIN type'). For clusters with mixed LLIN distribution, the number of LLINs from the dominant type received was divided by the total number of LLINs received in that cluster; non-study nets were excluded. To be included in the as-treated analyses, the proportion of the dominant LLIN had to be more than 75%. 'Cluster as-treated' analyses were presented as the main study findings.
codebook_description: Type of LLIN recieved for per protocol analysis

label: Cluster as-treated, dichotomized
definition: For households surveyed 6, 12, or 18 months after the 2016-2017 Universal Coverage Campaign (UCC), the type of long-lasting insecticide-treated bednet (LLIN) received by the cluster, for the as-treated analysis. Clusters received either conventional long-lasting insecticide-treated bednets (LLINs) or LLINs containing piperonyl butoxide (PBO). Conventional LLINs include PermaNet 2.0 and Olyset Net. PBO LLINs include PermaNet 3.0 and Olyset Plus. Certain clusters received a different LLIN type than that which was originally assigned to that cluster (the 'Cluster study arm'). For the as-treated analysis, clusters were grouped by type of LLINs received according to household data from the 6-month study timepoint ('UCC LLIN type'). For clusters with mixed LLIN distribution, the number of LLINs from the dominant type received was divided by the total number of LLINs received in that cluster; non-study nets were excluded. To be included in the as-treated analyses, the proportion of the dominant LLIN had to be more than 75%. 'Cluster as-treated' analyses were presented as the main study findings.
codebook_description: Intervention arm dichotomized for per protocol analysis

label: Dehydration, caregiver report
definition: Participant's dehydration level, as reported by the mother. No dehydration was defined as: non-sunken eyes, no lethargy, easily consoled if irritable, drinks or breastfeeds well, normal abdominal skin pinch. Some dehydration was defined as: irritable/difficult to console, delay in skin pinch return, eyes sunken, when offered liquid drinks eagerly/demonstrates greater than normal thirst. Severe dehydration was defined as: lethargy, sunken eyes, listless, difficulty in mother/child interaction. If the mother reported severe dehydration, the participant was referred to the nearest health center for assessment and treatment. Surveillance was conducted twice weekly for up to 3 years of age to assess illness on all days since the last surveillance visit.
codebook_description: Maternal report of dehydration (None=0, Some=1, Severe=2), original SAF data | Was children dehydrated? Maternal report of dehydration. From illness dataset. Source=illnessfull.csv. 1=yes;0=no
